depositCollateral(address,uint256).details: Caller must `approve` the CDP contract for `amount` prior to calling.

params.amount: The token amount to deposit (in token's smallest units).
params.token: The collateral token address (must be supported).

healthRatio(address,address).details: A value < `LIQUIDATION_THRESHOLD` means the position is eligible for liquidation.

liquidate(address,address,uint256).details: Liquidation can only occur when the health ratio is below `LIQUIDATION_THRESHOLD`.      The liquidator must have approved the CDP contract to transfer the stablecoin to be burned.

params.repayAmount: The stablecoin amount the liquidator wishes to repay on behalf of the user.

maxMintable(address,address).details: Returns 0 when no collateral or ratio set.

mint(address,uint256).details: The caller must have set a collateralization ratio >= `MIN_COLLATERAL_RATIO`.      The minted stablecoin is minted to the caller.

params.amount: The stablecoin amount to mint (18 decimals).
params.token: The collateral token used to back the minted stablecoin.

params.amount: The stablecoin amount to repay (18 decimals).

setCollateralizationRatio(address,uint25.details: `ratioPercent` must be >= `MIN_COLLATERAL_RATIO`. If the user already has debt,      the function will revert when the new ratio would make the position unsafe.

withdrawCollateral(address,uint256).details: Reverts if the withdrawal would make the remaining position undercollateralized      according to the caller's chosen collateralization ratio.

depositCollateral(address,uint256).notice: Deposit `amount` of `token` as collateral for the caller.

getPosition(address,address).notice: Returns `user`'s `token` position: collateral amount, debt, and collateral ratio percent.

healthRatio(address,address).notice: Returns the health ratio (percent) for `user`'s position in `token`.

liquidate(address,address,uint256).notice: Partially liquidate `user`'s position for `token` by repaying up to `repayAmount` of their debt.

maxMintable(address,address).notice: Returns the maximum amount of stablecoin the `user` may mint against `token` collateral         given their currently selected collateralization ratio for that token.

mint(address,uint256).notice: Mint `amount` of stablecoin against `token` collateral for the caller.

repay(uint256).notice: Repay `amount` of the caller's stablecoin debt. Caller must `approve` the CDP contract         to transfer their stablecoins. The contract pulls and burns the stablecoin and reduces         outstanding per-collateral debts proportionally.

setCollateralizationRatio(address,uint25.notice: Set the caller's desired collateralization ratio (percent) for `token`.

withdrawCollateral(address,uint256).notice: Withdraw `amount` of `token` collateral for the caller.
